result.execSummary:
The defendant Christina M. Stratton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:54 AM Defendant Christina M. Stratton in court.  Attorney Bryant S Plank in court for Christina M. Stratton.  Attorney Jensen in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a plea of No Contest. 22CF60, def enters a plea of No Contest. All other charges DRI. 
Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  She understood. Priors accurate.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. Felony warnings given.  She understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of  21CF195 -  Bail Jumping-Felony contrary to 946.49(1)(b). 22CF60 - Bail Jumping-Felony contrary to 946.49(1)(b). 939.62(1)(b) as repeaters.  

Joint recommendation: Withhold sentence, place on 2 yrs probation, risk and needs assessment as deemed appropriate by agent. 

Court adopts joint recommendation: Withholds sentence, orders 2 years probation on both cases concurrent. Follow thru and comply with any risk and needs assessment.  The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  CC, $250.00 cash bond on file, ordered applied to offset costs. Pay through probation. DNA already on file.

Court questioned defendant on her understanding of the waiver of preliminary hearing.  She stated she understood.  Court found that the defendant knowingly and intelligently waived her right to have a preliminary hearing.
